      "value": "<p><b>Source</b> <em>Ranged Tactics Toolbox pg. 0</em>, <em>Adventurer's Armory pg. 4</em>, <em>Advanced Player's Guide pg. 179</em>, <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 19</em></p><h3>Statistics</h3><p><b>Damage</b> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <b>Critical</b> x2; <b>Range</b> 20 ft.; <b>Type</b> P</p><p><b>Weapon Groups</b> Spears; Thrown</p><h3>Description</h3><p>The tip of this heavy javelin is designed to break off and embed itself into a shield once it hits. Like ammunition, a thrown pilum that hits its target is destroyed. If you hit a shieldbearing opponent with a pilum, he loses the AC bonuses from that shield until he takes a standard action to pry the remnants of the pilum from his shield.</p>"
